            <p>In 2016, the University of Bergen in Norway conducted a study on workaholism tied to psychiatric disorders on 16426 working adults.
            Results showed workaholics displayed a significant increase of psychiatric symptoms compared to non-workaholics.</p>
            <table class="table">
              <thead>
                <tr>
                  <th scope="col">Symptoms of:</th>
